Description: Fragment of a mould-made blue glazed composition (‘faience’) figure from cornice, plaque or statuette, perhaps from a larger composition. A rearing uraeus, with head broken away, wears the horns of Hathor and a sun disc crown, perhaps representing Renetutet.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: John de Monins Johnson
Curator's comments: For Roman period glazed composition, see Bulté 1991. Bulté, J. 1991. Talismans égyptiens d’heureuse maternité: ‘faïence’ bleu vert à pois foncés. Paris: Editions du Centre national de la recherche scientifique.
Bibliographic references: O'Connell et al 2014 / Antinoupolis at the British Museum (10)
